    body: "The Gloria is a non-biblical hymn of great antiquity, sometimes called the 'Greater Doxology,' beginning with the words the angels sang at Christ's birth (Luke 2:14). It is a hymn of praise and supplication addressed to each Person of the Trinity, expanding the angelic announcement into a full canticle of adoration. The Gloria is sung or recited on Sundays outside Advent and Lent, on solemnities, feasts, and at other solemn celebrations. Its omission during Advent and Lent makes its return at the Easter Vigil and Christmas particularly powerful. It dates to at least the fourth century and was originally a morning hymn before being incorporated into the Mass.",
