    body: "The Collect (from Latin collecta, 'gathered together') is the prayer proclaimed by the priest at the conclusion of the introductory rites, after the Gloria (when it is said) and the invitation 'Let us pray.' A period of silence follows the invitation, during which each member of the faithful formulates personal intentions; the priest then 'collects' these into a single prayer addressed to the Father, through the Son, in the Holy Spirit. The classic Roman Collect follows a precise structure: address to God, a relative clause recalling a divine attribute or action, a petition, and a Trinitarian conclusion. The Collects of the Roman Rite are renowned for their theological precision and literary beauty.",
