    oneLiner: "The prayer after Communion that asks God to bring to fruition in daily life the graces received in the Eucharist.",
    body: "The Post-Communion Prayer (oratio post communionem) is proclaimed by the priest after the period of sacred silence following the distribution of Communion. Like the Collect, it follows the classical Roman structure: address to God, a reference to what has been received, a petition for its fruits, and a Trinitarian conclusion. These prayers typically ask that the sacramental grace of Communion bear fruit in the lives of the faithful — healing, perseverance, charity, eternal life. They serve as a bridge between the liturgical celebration and the Christian life that must follow. The Post-Communion prayer is proper to each Mass and found in the Roman Missal.",
